RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JULY 25. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PHARAOH FANCY PANT raced in the three path around the first turn, chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two path, dueled down the lane and edged clear late. ONE EYED JACK saved ground around the first turn, led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the second bend and dug in in the stretch, giving way in the final strides. CATCHING FISH raced in the two path early, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the three path and finished evenly, no match for the top two. ENGLISH LAUGHTER raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack between horses, began a bid from the two path coming around the second turn and was outkicked in the lane. HONDO GUSTO trailed the field from the two path through the opening half mile, saved ground around the far bend and passed tiring horses in the stretch while never threatening. ESPECIALLEA saved ground around the first turn, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the second turn and was empty in the stretch. STAY HOME saved ground around the first bend, tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, dropped back coming around the far turn, entered the stretch in the four path and continued to tire from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 84. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE JULY 25. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 25 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAPSOLUTE dueled between horses up the backstretch, continued to battle from the three path around the turn and pulled clear in the stretch. LORD BARNA dueled on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the bend and kept on to the wire. LAUDERDALE trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and improved position in the lane. CHUCKY dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path around the bend and weakened in the final furlong. STUNNING BABY raced off the pace early, continued around the turn in the three path and was empty in the stretch. CHAOS KID tracked the leaders on the inside up the backstretch, dropped back around the turn, entered the stretch in the four path and tired further from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 93. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 19500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $12,500. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since December 25 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since Novem ber 25 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500 (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GREYZER raced in the two path around the first turn, trailed the field on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the five path nearing the quarter pole and dueled down the lane to get up for the win late. KING OF HOLLYWOOD raced in the two path early, stalked the pace setter on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the second bend and dueled in the lane, narrowly missing. HARD LIGHTING trailed the field on the inside through the opening half mile, began to move up while racing in the three path around the turn and continued to improve position in the stretch. SOMETHING NATURAL raced in the two path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, came around the far turn in the four path and kept on to the wire. I AM THAT I AM saved ground around the first turn, raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, began to improve position while saving ground around the far bend and was outkicked in the lane. CANDY COVE saved ground early, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, challenged from the two path coming around the second turn and weakened in the stretch. ARIES REIGNS showed the way from the three path around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the second bend and faded in the lane. A COTSWOLD VILLAGE raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace, dropped back to trail the field after a half mile had been run and was empty from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 79. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 23500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $25,000 OR LESS OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $25,000. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since November 25 Allowed 2 lbs. ; Since October 25 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Races Where Entered For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BEAUTY QUIST chased the leaders up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the turn and pulled clear in the final furlong. PARISIAN VIBE led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dueled while saving ground around the bend and chased the winner home late. HAPPY RIDE pressed the pace on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, dueled from the two path around the turn and kept on to the wire. ALEXA'S DREAM trailed the field early, began to improve position while racing in the two path around the turn and was outkicked in the lane. MOAM reared in the gate prior to the race, broke well and settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and never threatened. EPIC QUEEN raced in the middle of the pack between horses through the opening stages, saved ground around the turn and made no bid. BAZZARINA raced in the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the three path and faded in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 5 1 1/16M Turf CR: 81. Claiming Purse 19600. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since December 25 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Races Where Entered For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Condition Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COOL FRONT raced in the two path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far bend still in the two path, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and pulled clear on the rail. A RING THING raced in the two path early, pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the second turn and kept on to the finish. ASTERS D'ORO bumped with the horse to her inside leaving the gate, recovered to duel from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued to battle from the rail around the far turn and weakened late. AZIZA saved ground early, tracked the leaders between horses up the backstretch, came around the far bend in the three path and finished evenly. MISS Z saved ground around the first turn, trailed the field on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two path and gained ground mildly in the stretch. SUMMER AT THE SPA saved ground around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, began a bid from the four path coming off the far turn and was outfinished late. ENTWINE (IRE) brushed with the horse to her inside at the break, settled off the pace in the two path through the opening half mile, came around the far bend in the three path and was empty in the stretch. KEKE KIMONO bumped with the horses to both sides leaving the gate, recovered to lead the field while saving ground early, dropped back after a half mile had been run and tired from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 6 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 100. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 28000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $32,000. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since Dece mber 25 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since November 25 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000 (Races Where Entered For $25,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ITS A WRAP raced in the three path around the first turn, dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path around the far bend, kicked clear entering the stretch and drew off to the wire. BUMPERDOO raced in the three path through the opening quarter of a mile, trailed the field on the outside up the backstretch, improved position while saving ground around the far turn and continued to gain in the lane while proving to be no match for the winner. HELIUM raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn still in the two path, began a bid nearing the quarter pole and finished evenly. INDIAN FEVER led the way from the two path around the first turn, dueled on the rail up the backstretch and around the second bend and faded in the stretch. PRENDIMI saved ground early, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, began to drop back while saving ground around the far turn and tired further in the lane.

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Castle Park Farm, LLC & Breffni Farm

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 7 1M Turf CR: 89. Claiming Purse 20500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since December 25 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since November 25 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Co nsidered) (Condition Eligibility). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PANOTTI raced in the two path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the outside, began a bid from the four path coming around the second turn and gained ground to get up for the win in late stretch. LENTEN ROSE saved ground around the first bend, chased the leader up the backstretch, challenged from the rail coming around the far turn, kicked clear entering the stretch and was caught near the wire. MIZZEN ASH saved ground early, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the four path, began a bid nearing the quarter pole and gained ground late. PACIFIC PRINCESS stalked the pace setter from the two path through the opening half mile, began a bid from the three path coming around the far bend and was outkicked in the final furlong. SWEET MOOCHIE raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch at the back of the pack on the inside, saved ground around the far bend and passed tiring horses in the stretch. KITTEN WITH A WHIP raced in the middle of the pack between horses around the first turn and up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the two path and weakened in late stretch. SHE B GLAMOROUS raced in the two path around the first turn, trailed the field on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the far bend still in the two path and made no bid. MAKE NO MISTAKE led the way on the inside around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled while saving ground around the far turn and tired entering the stretch. ONE NIGHT STAND raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, came around the far turn still in the three path and was empty in the lane. DONYA'S MAGIC raced in the three path early, pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, dropped back while racing in the two path around the second bend and faded further from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 93. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE JULY 25. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 25 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BAZOO dueled on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn, kicked clear in upper stretch and held off a late closer at the wire. ROOKIE SALSA chased the leaders between horses through the opening quarter of a mile, raced in the four path around the bend and gained ground late. MR LIGHTNING BOY raced off the pace early, navigated the turn from the two path and improved position in the lane. ARCADIA CALLS pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, dueled from the three path around the bend and in upper stretch and weakened in the final furlong. ODDS ON trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and never fired. I KICKN dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle while saving ground around the bend and tired in the lane. LITIGANT raced in the middle of the pack in the early going, continued around the turn in the three path and was empty from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 9 5F Turf CR: 89. Maiden Special Weight Purse 27000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $25,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $25,000 And Since Then Have Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $25,000 Or More.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EXPLOSIVE EXCHANGE led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the turn and dug in in the stretch to hold the win. SWEET TRACK tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the two path coming around the bend and dueled down the lane but could not get by the winner. DRAGONERA pressed the pace on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the turn and kept on to the finish. MOMMY JUICE raced in the middle of the pack on the outside early, navigated the turn from the two path and improved position mildly in the stretch. MOTOWN MIKA veered out leaving the gate, angled in to chase the leaders on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and was outkicked in the final furlong. BROKEN HEARTS BAY trailed the field on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the bend and passed tiring horses in the lane. ONE TOUGH DAME bumped with the horses to both sides leaving the gate, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, came around the turn in the two path and made no bid. ROMANTIC FANTASY bumped mildly with the horse to her inside at the start, raced at the back of the pack early, saved ground around the turn and showed no kick. BEAST BUNNY veered in and bumped with the horse to her inside at the break, settled in the middle of the pack for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and faded from there. HEAVEN'S D'ORO raced at the back of the pack on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, angled in to save ground around the bend and was empty in the stretch.
